Indeed i do feel like the Akali rework is gonna be busted but it's a very unique rework. Her w lasts for 5 seconds instead of 8 and no teleport when casting w (however ult does cover shrouds teleport). Her w is still very busted though because she is detectable but untargetable including under turret range which is quite insane but if you think about it Vladimir can do something similar.
However what I really like about a disadvantage of Akali is that she has to use almost all her abilities to kill one enemy and this may stop her from 1v9 everybody there. But if this is good if she is for e.g near baron pit and e, r q the combo... w to keep her agility and hide whenever she needs to. Ever since the assasin update came its been really good and has affected Akali quite significantly. 
I feel like Akali won't be really broken but will pick up loads of hype just like the aatrox rework so dw im hyped too.{{champion:84}}
